CAUTION! PLEASE READ! Very disappointing. MANAGER IS RUDE. I had a negative experience with the coffee I was served, and politely asked the store manger if he would remake the drink. After the cashier confirmed she'd sold me the coffee, I was required to show proof that I purchased the drink in that location using various methods. The manager wanted to see the sticker adhered to the actual cup, and my DD rewards app to verify the time of purchase. He agreed to correct the problem and acted as if he was doing me a favor while they served everyone in the store before helping me. Whats worse is the manager left my coffee sitting while he went to the back to take a phone call. The customer service and products are lacking. If this store was not located in close proximity to the Metro, they wouldn't be able to keep the doors open! Starbucks is right across the street. Go there for coffee instead and AVOID THIS DUNKIN LOCATION AT ALL COST!!!!

I came in here today after a short visit at my doctors office who happens to be in the same office complex. I actually stumbled upon this cafe, and since I was already in the mood for an iced latte, I figured it would be a good idea to stop on by.  There were already quite a few customers already inside of the store waiting to place their order, but nevertheless Dina was ready and waiting to take my order. She told me about the different types of bagels and bagel spreads that thy offered here. It was cool so I ordered the pllain bagel with strawberry cream cheese. I also got the iced signature latte. It took the three employees behind the counter a matter of minutes to have everything prepared and ready to go. The bagel toasted great by the way!
This was probably the  best experience I've had at this Dunkin. The signature drinks that I ordered were made perfectly!

I am a long time customer of this location, but I will never be going back.  Today, a strange man approached me from behind while I waited at the counter for my order to be taken.  He told me I was beautiful and hugged me.  When I stepped away from him and asked him not to hug me, he began shouting that I was a white supremacist.  The staff member at the counter then took my order, which I regret paying for.  I turn away from the counter to the pick-up area, and the strange man is pointing to his wife and again yelling that I am a white supremacist and shouting 'GIT, GIT, GIT!'  Zero staff members said anything, as I was chased out of this location by a deranged man who felt it was appropriate to touch a stranger.
